HEADWORD: Tripartient
<hw>Tri*par"tient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Tripartite</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Arith.)</fld> <def>Dividing into three
parts; -- said of a number which exactly divides another into three
parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

